        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 4:51PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 451 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Clarkesville, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clarkesville, Demorest, Mount Airy, and Hollywood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
